name: Super-Ego

In psychology, the superego, as defined by Sigmund Freud, is the part of the psyche that acts as a conscience and regulates socially appropriate behavior. This may be yet another reference to the film Forbidden Planet, wherein the creature killing crewmembers is described as "Monsters from the Id."
